01:17.750 --> 01:21.600
And just for the record,I
don't think you're wrong.

01:22.510 --> 01:24.770
I just happen to agree with him.

01:24.840 --> 01:27.200
That's the fourth time he's
"happened" to agree with you.

01:27.300 --> 01:31.020
Look,you wanted a bench trial
to protect him from a jury.

01:31.240 --> 01:34.210
You want an expedited hearing
to protect him from the press.

01:34.260 --> 01:38.180
Now you want to keep him off the stand
to protect him from cross-examination.

01:38.590 --> 01:41.830
He needs a litigator,taylor,not
an overprotective daughter.

01:41.920 --> 01:43.970
Oh,what about an overeager prot?

01:44.030 --> 01:46.760
who blames himself for
the mess his mentor's in?

01:46.810 --> 01:48.470
He still has the support of the board.

01:48.550 --> 01:51.530
How long do you think that'll last
the longer this thing drags out?

01:51.640 --> 01:54.690
It's just too bad that no outside firm
will get in the middle of this,huh?

01:54.800 --> 01:56.840
Yeah,it's too bad.

01:57.890 --> 01:59.700
This is me.

01:59.800 --> 02:01.770
- Good night.
- Good night.

02:09.240 --> 02:10.750
god.

02:10.900 --> 02:13.710
Yes,I'm rather anxious myself.

02:13.770 --> 02:18.380
In moments such as these-- not that I've been
fortunate to have any on quite this scale--

02:18.440 --> 02:20.660
I find it best to focus on the client.

02:20.740 --> 02:21.640
The client?

02:21.740 --> 02:24.600
Yes,the client,eli-- the
individual,or,in this case,

02:24.670 --> 02:28.210
individuals who have retained
our services on their behalf.

02:28.270 --> 02:30.710
Because of the thing with the,uh,case.

02:30.960 --> 02:33.790
I'm not getting an overwhelming
feeling of confidence here.

02:33.890 --> 02:35.570
It's okay,sir.

02:37.310 --> 02:39.260
I'm ready for...trial.

02:39.350 --> 02:41.110
I'm just not sure what that trial is.

02:44.180 --> 02:48.120
eli,you're about to face nine
justices who are going to,at a minimum,

02:48.200 --> 02:52.300
expect you to appreciate the distinction
between them and a state court.

02:52.380 --> 02:53.670
"Them," sir?

02:53.870 --> 02:56.510
Sorry,could you be more personal
with your personal pronouns?

02:56.930 --> 03:01.540
Eli,we're less than an hour from arguing a
case before the highest court in the land.

03:01.610 --> 03:04.950
The phrase "get on the
ball" comes to mind.

03:23.650 --> 03:25.010
matt?

03:25.160 --> 03:28.130
I heard that jordan wants to cut back
associate salaries by nearly half.

03:28.230 --> 03:29.610
Not my business,tommy.

03:29.720 --> 03:30.740
Sure it is.

03:30.840 --> 03:32.210
You're the one sleeping
with the enemy...

03:32.280 --> 03:33.810
or at least his daughter.

03:34.060 --> 03:37.530
So is wethersby gonna bankrupt this
place and us along with it,or not?

03:38.140 --> 03:41.020
No,he's not.all right,he
built this place.

03:41.090 --> 03:43.610
He put that rolex on your wrist
and that designer suit on your back.

03:43.660 --> 03:47.400
You don't have any of that without
him,so show the man some respect.

03:53.910 --> 03:55.220
Taylor.

03:55.460 --> 03:59.120
Just out of curiosity,did I miss any
classic matt dowd zingers just now?

03:59.170 --> 04:01.700
Or did you remain completely
silent the entire time?

04:01.770 --> 04:04.390
Tommy was just venting some
very understandable anxieties.

04:04.420 --> 04:05.580
"Sleeping with the enemy"?

04:05.630 --> 04:06.960
He's your dad,and they
know we're together.

04:06.990 --> 04:10.200
Whatever I said wouldn't have mattered
because I'm not seen as objective,

04:10.270 --> 04:13.300
and you've got the same problem.

04:13.370 --> 04:14.950
Excuse me?

04:15.080 --> 04:16.860
In court.

04:16.950 --> 04:21.779
You're his daughter,taylor,and any argument you make
to a judge is going to lose credibility because of that.

04:21.820 --> 04:22.700
You sound like eli.

04:22.810 --> 04:25.790
And if he and I actually agree,that
should really tell you something.

04:25.930 --> 04:27.820
You know,this isn't
really helpful right now.

04:27.900 --> 04:30.620
You don't need to represent your dad
to prove to him you're a great lawyer.

04:30.810 --> 04:33.350
The psychoanalysis isn't helping either.

04:33.380 --> 04:37.130
Taylor... I'm gonna stay at my place
tonight.I've got a lot of work to do.

04:38.330 --> 04:40.030
Okay.

04:41.540 --> 04:44.100
Well,maybe this is the one that
takes you to the supreme court.

04:44.160 --> 04:45.500
What?

04:45.970 --> 04:48.210
Oh,you've got vision fever.

04:48.890 --> 04:50.920
I must have missed that
day at medical school.

04:51.010 --> 04:53.980
You had a vision last week.You
read a little bit of dad's journal.

04:54.010 --> 04:55.510
It's all cool and exciting.

04:55.580 --> 04:56.550
You got the prophet bug.

04:56.670 --> 04:58.600
Will you stop making up
spiritual ailments,please?

04:58.640 --> 05:00.330
I-I have no time for
new cases right now,nate.

05:00.370 --> 05:02.720
I got my plate full with
posner and klein vs.Wethersby.

05:02.770 --> 05:05.150
Just come with me to
see my new patient,okay?

05:05.260 --> 05:07.630
I'll have you in and out of the
clinic in,like,less than an hour.

05:07.710 --> 05:09.180
- Clinic?
- Yeah,I told you.

05:09.280 --> 05:10.700
I'm volunteering at the
park presidio free clinic.

05:10.800 --> 05:12.080
Since when?

05:12.190 --> 05:13.960
Well,ever since you saved
me from the aneurysm,

05:14.000 --> 05:17.150
I guess I figured I
should give something back.

05:17.190 --> 05:19.860
All right,so this patient I've been
seeing--she's only 6 years old,all right?

05:19.980 --> 05:23.090
She lives with her family in a low-income
housing unit in the tenderloin--you know,

05:23.150 --> 05:25.670
the kind where the paint's been peeling
off the walls for the last 30 years?

05:25.700 --> 05:27.760
In fact,that's why she needs you.

05:27.800 --> 05:29.280
She's got lead poisoning?

05:29.330 --> 05:31.000
Serious health problems.

05:31.070 --> 05:33.610
It's impossible to prove
causation in lead paint cases.

05:33.640 --> 05:37.420
And even if you could,the C.P.S.C.
Made lead paint illegal in 1978,

05:37.680 --> 05:40.430
which means the statute of
limitations has already expired.

05:40.490 --> 05:44.060
- Yeah,but,eli
- but thank you,and keep those great suggestions coming.

05:44.190 --> 05:45.730
I gotta get back to the office.

05:45.800 --> 05:47.680
eli?

05:57.810 --> 06:00.380
"equal justice under law."

06:00.730 --> 06:04.790
The equal protection clause was written
exactly for a case like this one--

06:04.840 --> 06:09.620
for people struggling agnst powerful
interests arrayed against them.

06:09.770 --> 06:14.160
This is the pinnacle of my
career,eli-- of any attorney's career.

06:14.880 --> 06:17.010
But for you,I'd be on the other side,

06:17.200 --> 06:20.680
representing the likes of
the L.P.M.A.I'd be dishonoring

06:20.720 --> 06:24.830
these hallowed halls with a halfhearted
argument defending the constitutional

06:24.950 --> 06:28.820
right of paint manufacturers
to poison innoce children.

06:29.770 --> 06:32.210
This is the lead paint case.

06:32.740 --> 06:35.900
Try not to sound so surprised.

06:36.940 --> 06:38.670
ElI!Eli?

06:40.080 --> 06:41.650
Vision?

06:42.100 --> 06:43.650
No.

06:43.800 --> 06:45.400
Yeah.

06:45.520 --> 06:46.370
Uh,you could tell?

06:46.440 --> 06:47.250
Yeah,you had vision face.

06:47.350 --> 06:50.420
- And now who's making up ailments?
- Okay,so what did you see?

06:50.420 --> 06:52.850
Was it--I mean,was
it about my case?

06:53.010 --> 06:54.830
It was about my
case,wasn't it?-I knew it.

06:54.920 --> 06:56.430
How could you p

